1
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,829
{\an8}It's always about Mikoy.

2
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:39,164
{\an8}Is that really how it is?

3
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:41,416
{\an8}Are you willing to die just for Mikoy?

4
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:44,919
{\an8}<i>He's important to the case we're building</i>
<i>against the Moravianos.</i>

5
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:50,842
{\an8}Hey! You devil.

6
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:15,784
{\an8}<i>I will finish him myself!</i>

7
00:01:20,121 --> 00:01:21,122
{\an8}Hey!

8
00:01:23,124 --> 00:01:24,000
{\an8}I actually need your help.

9
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,251
{\an8}Wait, was that a gunshot?

10
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:27,212
{\an8}- Because I was followed.
- By who?

11
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:28,505
{\an8}La Fornarina!

12
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:29,631
{\an8}Mikoy!

13
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:48,108
{\an8}Mikoy!

14
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:57,867
{\an8}Mikoy?

15
00:02:02,664 --> 00:02:03,665
{\an8}Mikoy!

16
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:11,464
{\an8}We received a report
about a road rage incident,

17
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:14,008
{\an8}which apparently led to a shootout,

18
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:16,970
{\an8}and we recovered several shell casings.

19
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:21,391
{\an8}But the drivers of both vehicles
have already fled.

20
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,895
{\an8}Agent Sianong, team.

21
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,438
{\an8}We need to spread out quickly.

22
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:28,857
{\an8}Our asset is being hunted.

23
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:31,192
{\an8}Okay. Thank you.

24
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:32,110
{\an8}Sir.

25
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:35,363
{\an8}Men, back to work.

26
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:36,364
{\an8}Sir.

27
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,390
{\an8}Mikoy!

28
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,864
Hey! Who are you?

29
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,366
You're a thief, aren't you?

30
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:02,533
No. Sir…

31
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,911
Please don't make noise.
I'm not a thief, I promise.

32
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:07,038
You have the nerve to lie!

33
00:04:07,121 --> 00:04:08,414
Stay right there! Don't move.

34
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:10,792
- Please.
- You're even kneeling now?

35
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,335
This isn't a Quiapo Church!

36
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:43,533
Just relax?

37
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:44,909
That's what's on your mind?

38
00:04:44,993 --> 00:04:46,160
In a situation like this?

39
00:04:46,244 --> 00:04:47,453
Aren't you worried?

40
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:48,997
Doesn't that bother you?

41
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,416
Mikoy is a freaking spy!

42
00:05:08,891 --> 00:05:10,184
I don't know.

43
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:12,061
I don't know.

44
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:13,646
Can't we do anything?

45
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:14,897
Is there nothing we can do, Viktor?

46
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,487
What are you talking about?

47
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:06,866
That's what you’re worrying about?!

48
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,814
Mikoy.

49
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:09,637
Well, you must be Kim Dominguez.

50
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:14,308
Or Kim Santo Domingo.

51
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:20,982
All I know is you look exactly
like the person I hate most!

52
00:07:35,163 --> 00:07:37,206
You never really understood
your daughter, did you?

53
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:43,087
You don't understand her!

54
00:07:43,171 --> 00:07:44,714
No!

55
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:48,885
Because if you truly
understood your daughter,

56
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:52,513
you'd know how painful this is.

57
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:56,267
You'd know how painful
what we're making her do is.

58
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:57,935
Viktor.

59
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:03,024
She's about to kill the person
she loves the most.

60
00:08:10,781 --> 00:08:13,618
Chiara, please don't make me hurt you.

61
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:31,135
Chiara, please. Stop. Let's talk.

62
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:47,318
Here. A heart for a heart!

63
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:19,850
Be a father to your daughter! To Chiara.

64
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:21,602
Treat her like your daughter.

65
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:28,818
Not a weapon that you keep using
to take down your enemies.

66
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:34,407
I'm sorry, my love.

67
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,799
Viktor.

68
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:55,428
She's our daughter.

69
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:05,146
Mikoy!

70
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:16,991
Mikoy, don’t run. Let’s end this!

71
00:10:44,894 --> 00:10:45,895
Mikoy?

72
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:51,108
Mikoy.

73
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:13,672
Agent Alex, are you okay?

74
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,549
You shouldn't be here.

75
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:17,718
I can handle this.

76
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:24,809
Sir, our agency teammates are here.

77
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:27,019
Maybe you can tell them
what happened again.

78
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,021
Well,

79
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,399
there was a man and a woman.

80
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:35,069
The woman was chasing
some guy who looked like an idiot.

81
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:37,113
Then, all of a sudden,

82
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:38,781
the woman started shooting at him.

83
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:41,450
Looks like Chiara really wanted
to finish Mikoy off.

84
00:11:42,451 --> 00:11:43,536
Ma'am, no.

85
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:47,581
That's not how we see it.

86
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:50,251
What do you mean, not really?

87
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:57,550
Mikoy! Did you miss me, hon?

88
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,222
What's that?

89
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,307
A lovers' quarrel?

90
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:06,851
Pretty brutal, huh?

91
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:08,060
It really is.

92
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,770
If you ask me, ma'am,

93
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:11,439
they seemed like a married couple.

94
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,399
A toxic married couple.

95
00:12:13,482 --> 00:12:14,442
The kind where

96
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:17,236
the husband did something wrong,
so the wife chased him down.

97
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:19,029
Just to scare him

98
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,282
because he screwed her over.

99
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:29,874
Mikoy, does it hurt?

100
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:42,887
You're just too violent.

101
00:12:46,474 --> 00:12:47,808
I'm sorry!

102
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:50,144
- Sorry. Sorry.
- I'm gonna destroy you.

103
00:12:50,227 --> 00:12:52,104
- Freaking liar!
- You were trying to shoot me!

104
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,231
- Liar!
- Can we talk first?

105
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:57,693
Please, let's talk first.

106
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:04,241
Screwed her over?

107
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:08,370
Screwed her over. Lied to her.
Gaslighted her. Cheated on her.

108
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:10,039
I don't know about you kids these days.

109
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:11,916
You're always on your phones.

110
00:13:11,999 --> 00:13:14,168
That's why now, you're all clueless.

111
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:16,921
Airheads. Idiots.

112
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:20,424
You know?

113
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:23,302
You don't spend enough time
hanging out on street corners.

114
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:24,637
Sir.

115
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:26,680
- What happened next?
- Oh, right.

116
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,933
Anyway, the woman was furious.

117
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:30,184
She was yelling.

118
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:31,685
She said to the man,

119
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:33,646
"How dare you call me 'my love'?"

120
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:36,815
And the man replied,

121
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,108
"Chiara,

122
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:40,653
please stop. Let's talk about this."

123
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:43,239
So the woman didn't stop?

124
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:45,783
Bro, I told you, they're toxic.

125
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:49,036
For most couples,

126
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:50,746
they'd just throw plates.

127
00:13:50,829 --> 00:13:52,873
These two were shooting at each other.

128
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:55,459
- Oh God.
- That's dangerous.

129
00:13:55,543 --> 00:13:57,086
But wait.

130
00:13:57,836 --> 00:13:59,255
I think

131
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:01,173
if she really wanted to kill the guy,

132
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:02,424
he would've been dead already.

133
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:05,636
- Right? Besides,
- Exactly.

134
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,930
it still looked like
they loved each other.

135
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,682
The only problem is,

136
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:11,517
they both seem crazy.

137
00:14:14,144 --> 00:14:15,104
Right?

138
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:21,026
Let's talk first, okay?

139
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,111
Talk?

140
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:25,322
- You want to talk?!
- Wait.

141
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:26,615
You're really going to throw that?

142
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:30,911
You won't do it. You don't have it in you.

143
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,922
Was that part of your training?

144
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:44,425
Was that also part of lying to me?

145
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,468
Where's Mikoy?

146
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,262
Why? Didn't he tell you?

147
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,763
He never went to the office.

148
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:57,563
<i>Yes, ma'am. Mr. Pinagpala</i>
<i>hasn't reported to the office yet.</i>

149
00:14:57,646 --> 00:15:00,065
If you didn't go to the office,
where did you go?

150
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:03,110
I left the house
to meet up with my friends.

151
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,367
<i>Mikoy, listen to me carefully.</i>

152
00:15:15,623 --> 00:15:17,750
No! I'm only a police asset.

153
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,543
Alex just taught me some self-defense.

154
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:23,255
- Alex?
- Oops.

155
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:24,506
I mean, Sianong!

156
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,841
- Yes, Sianong.
- Alex?!

157
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:27,051
And Alex too.

158
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:28,427
Alex!

159
00:16:11,553 --> 00:16:12,596
Bok.

160
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:16,350
They said there were more gunshots
near a grocery store.

161
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:17,977
I think it's still Chiara.

162
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,024
Hey. Bok.

163
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:27,361
Dara, Rafa.

164
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:29,530
Quick!

165
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:31,532
What happened?

166
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:33,909
The bandages are loose.
They need to rewrap them.

167
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:35,869
You talk to all the witnesses.

168
00:16:35,953 --> 00:16:37,579
Police, SWAT, everyone.

169
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:39,665
Wait, what happened?

170
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:42,793
My God. Let me see.

171
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:54,179
- Boo.
- Ah! Good Lord.

172
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:03,439
Looks like you can't sleep either.

173
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,362
Viktor.

174
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:12,906
My goodness!

175
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,501
Or maybe she already did.

176
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:43,395
Do it.

177
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:47,107
Isn't this your mission?

178
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:22,684
Dara. Put more bandages on her.

179
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:24,394
She can't afford to lose
even a drop more blood.

180
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:25,437
Do it now.

181
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:26,605
I'm still coming.

182
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:28,440
- It's just a bandage replacement.
- No, Bok!

183
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:29,608
No, okay?

184
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:31,693
Dara, take her back to the hospital.

185
00:18:32,736 --> 00:18:34,113
You can't order me around.

186
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:37,032
And I won't let myself lose
someone I love again.

187
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:49,795
Bok. Bok.

188
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:53,215
Bok, let me handle
tracking down Mikoy, okay?

189
00:18:53,298 --> 00:18:56,176
I promise you, I'll bring him back alive.

190
00:18:59,304 --> 00:19:00,430
Go on, Dara.

191
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:13,026
You're wrong about me.

192
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:16,071
I'm still me.

193
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:19,491
The Mikoy you came to know.

194
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:50,147
Maybe you never really knew me.

195
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:19,259
Goodbye, Mr. Michael "Mikoy"

196
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:24,556
D. Pinagpala!

197
00:21:38,171 --> 00:21:39,381
So, what now?

198
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,552
Can we talk now?

199
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:48,974
Huh?

200
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:17,669
<i>We found the place where Mikoy</i>
<i>and La Fornarina fought.</i>

201
00:22:23,091 --> 00:22:25,218
Looks like the two had an intense fight.

202
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:30,599
<i>I already sent a sweeper team</i>
<i>to spread out</i>

203
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:35,771
<i>to also search for traces</i>
<i>that Chiara and Mikoy is there.</i>

204
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:39,900
Whatever you said,
you can’t change the fact

205
00:22:39,983 --> 00:22:43,820
that you fooled me and lied to me.

206
00:22:46,448 --> 00:22:50,869
The reason I’m doing all this
is to protect you from your family

207
00:22:51,369 --> 00:22:54,081
in this world of yours.

208
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,835
<i>That’s Mikoy and Chiara! Let’s get them!</i>

209
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:02,255
I do.

210
00:23:04,007 --> 00:23:05,050
Let’s call Agent Sianong.

